So we only have 1 and a half day left and I'm super excited.. AND emily is getting her car fixed and we finally get to go to Quincy by ourselves on Tuesday!!!! :D 

I had quite a busy weekend..

1) On Friday, Emily and I went to Walmart and such, got some matching flip flops. Also had the bathroom changing accident! :P

2) Spent Friday night with Emily, I did her biology homework and her teacher didn't even know the difference. That was hilarious. Then we went to the hot dog thing lol.

3) Saturday night, we had supper over at Laci and DJ's. Also watched 13 going on 30..good movie.

4) Sunday I got to drive a tractor down to Hydesburg Church. Before that I had to mow..got darker, (Like I need anymore! on my arms anway.)

Then Monday was boring..but I've been rather happy all week seeing as it is the last week of school. We watched Tommy Boy in Marketing and took a test. Then in Biology we took the final, which I don't think I did so well on because it was the end of class and I was rushing. Then in Spanish we watch Field of Dreams and it actually WASN'T IN SPANISH THIS TIME!!! shocker I know, but it did have spanish subtitles, but after awhile you just block them out.

Tuesday was realllly boring. I had IBS, but I was in the Patterson because so many people are in IBS they have to have two rooms. Sad really, and who gives IBS on the last week of school anyways? I didn't have anything to work on either so it made it worse. At least I got to go up and finish my final in Geometry. I was actually happy to be up there for once. Then I had to go back down and then I had to come back up and take my English final. I think I actually did pretty good on it. Then for the next 3 hours I was bored out of my mind and half asleep. But I couldn't sleep. Then for lunch we only got to eat for 10 minutes because we were in between shifts, isolated from everyone. Pretty pathedic if you ask me. Megan and I were writing back and forth and playing tic tac toe. 

Well gotta go, bell's about to ring.
